        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I wanted to start a grip thread on the New UI. Not because I don't like it but to assemble some useful things we could point out to VI. I happen to like the new UI very much but just wish the following could be addressed.</P><P>1) Cannot target things through the windows. Big problem for chanters and clerics. I don't like this at all. You could do this in the old transparent screens</P><P>2) Some of the icons need to be corrected (necro). For starters Pact of Shadow should not be the exact same as Bonds of Death. Those two are not the same line of spell. In the old book one was a heal icon and the other was a Tap line icon.</P><P>3) An added step in the corpse looting. Is it just me or did we used to be able to finish looting by clicking the "Done" button on the inventory window? Now I keep doing that and find myself having to go over and click the "Done" button on the corpse window as well. minor pain but like a pimple on the nose it's a constant reminder...</P><P>4) Text in "New Windows" will not fade. In the old UI it was perfect that the window using the "/hitsmode" command could be unclickable, and the text would fade after a given number of seconds. I use to have my melee others text go to that 5 line window in the old UI and tried the /hitsmode command in the new UI and it seems changed or disabled? Anyone have luck in this or find a way to have the text fade, then lock the window in place so it would be there the next time you logged in?</P><P>More to come I am sure.....but VI did a great job on the new UI and it has the feel of playing a new game.</P><P>Tappe<BR>Saryn Server</P><P> </font></td>

