         The /bazaar interface **NEEDS** to auto-update itself. The items for sale after they've been bought will NOT go away from the listing until the player STOPS his trading, and restarts it. Updating vendors just adds more vendors that arent on the list already. It needs to update *every single vendors and their items for sale* .. Real-Time if possible. It's too cumbersome at the moment trying to buy stuff with 400+ people in the zone and the item lists are NOT updating. By the time you find the person the item is gone, but it's still on the list. ANNOYING. Also the /bazaar window NEEDS to be adjustable. It's TOO SMALL at 1028x1024. Another bug it has is sometimes the first 5 lines will be blank, and you need to hit the down arrow to have it refresh and display them.</P><P>Spell icons, we so need an option to toggle between the old and new icons. These new ones are just horrible. They're not crisp pictures, and they're hard to make out. The old ones were simple because they reused the same icons for the same spell lines. </P><P>LAG .. The engine needs an overhaul again to speed up Bazaar with 400 people in it .. How the HECK is this going to work in EQ2 when the models are 5 times more complex? I hope they've got Carmack doing their engine!</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
